18/07/2005
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The European Commission announced on Friday (15 July) that it has decided to launch proceedings against Greece for breaching the EU environmental law. 
According to a statement on the EU Web site, six different cases related to the Greek government's management of wastewater, air pollution, solid waste, noise impact assessment and access to information that have fallen short of EU guidelines. 
The Commission also wants to refer Greece to the European Court of Justice for failing to limit emissions that harm the ozone layer. 
(Kathimerini - 16/07/05; EU Web site - 15/07/05)
